  "text": "42 Because 14-3-3 family members lack innate catalytic activity and exert their regulatory functions largely through binding target ligands to inactivate them or alter their localization, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] we hypothesize that the regulatory activity of 14-3-3z on FoxM1 may be through the inhibition or sequestration of an inhibitor or competitor of FoxM1, [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] allowing FoxM1 activity to increase under conditions of increased oxidative stress.",
